5. [Networking and Security](#networking-and-security)
6. [Storage Management](#storage-management)
7. [Miscellaneous Commands](#miscellaneous-commands)


## 1. ESXi Host Commands

| Command                                    | Description                      | Usage                                        |
|--------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| `vmware -v`                                | Check ESXi version               | Display the installed ESXi version.          |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/getallvms`                  | List all VMs on the host         | Show all virtual machines on the host.       |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/power.on <VMID>`            | Power on a VM                    | Power on a specific virtual machine.         |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/power.off <VMID>`           | Power off a VM                   | Power off a specific virtual machine.        |
| `services.sh restart`                      | Restart management agents        | Restart ESXi host management agents.         |
| `esxcli network nic list`                  | List network interfaces          | Show all network interfaces on the host.     |
| `esxcli network ip connection list`        | View active network connections  | Display active network connections.          |
| `esxcli hardware platform get`             | Check host uptime                | Display the ESXi host uptime.                |
| `esxcli hardware get`                      | Get hardware information         | Show detailed hardware info for the host.    |
| `esxcli system health status get`          | Check system health              | Show the health status of the host.          |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/hostsummary`              | View host configuration          | Display the summary of host configuration.   |
| `esxcli hardware cpu list`                 | Show CPU information             | Display detailed CPU information.            |
| `esxcli memory get`                        | Show memory usage                | Display memory usage on the host.            |
| `esxcli software vib list`                 | List installed patches           | Show all installed patches and VIBs.         |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/configinfo`               | Get host configuration           | Display the current host configuration.      |


---

## 2. VM and Resource Management

| Command                                                              | Description                      | Usage                                             |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/migrate <VMID> <destination_host>`                    | Migrate a VM using vMotion       | Move a VM to another host via vMotion.            |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/snapshot.get <VMID>`                                  | List VM snapshots                | Show all snapshots for a VM.                      |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/snapshot.create <VMID> <snapshot_name> <description>` | Create a snapshot                | Create a VM snapshot with a name and description. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/snapshot.removeall <VMID>`                            | Remove all snapshots             | Delete all VM snapshots.                          |
| `esxtop`                                                             | Monitor ESXi performance         | Monitor ESXi CPU and memory usage.                |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/get.resource <VMID>`                                  | View VM resources                | Show resource allocations for a VM.               |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/nic.add <VMID> <adapter_type> <network_name>`         | Add a network adapter            | Add a NIC to a VM.                                |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/reconfig <VMID> <new_config>`                         | Reconfigure VM resources         | Change resource settings for a VM.                |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/clone <VMID> <new_name>`                              | Clone a VM                       | Duplicate an existing VM.                         |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/create <VM_Name> <Datastore> <VM_ID>`                 | Create a VM                      | Create a new VM.                                  |

---

## 3. ESXi Host Maintenance

| Command                                                    | Description               | Usage                                      |
|------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/maintenance_mode_enter`                   | Enable maintenance mode    | Put the ESXi host into maintenance mode.   |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/maintenance_mode_exit`                    | Exit maintenance mode      | Take the ESXi host out of maintenance mode.|
| `reboot`                                                   | Reboot ESXi host           | Reboot the ESXi host.                      |
| `shutdown`                                                 | Shutdown ESXi host         | Shutdown the ESXi host.                    |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/services list`                            | List services              | Show all services running on the host.     |
| `esxcli system hostname set --host=<new_hostname>`         | Change hostname            | Set a new hostname for the ESXi host.      |
| `esxcli system maintenanceMode set --enable`               | Enable maintenance mode    | Enable maintenance mode for the host.      |


---

## 4. Troubleshooting and Logs

## 4. Troubleshooting and Logs

| Command                                                    | Description                | Usage                                         |
|------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| `cat /var/log/vmkernel.log`                                | View ESXi logs             | Show ESXi system logs.                        |
| `tail -f /vmfs/volumes/<datastore>/<vm_name>/vmware.log`   | Check VM logs              | View log files for a specific VM.             |
| `esxcli system syslog config get`                          | View hardware logs         | Show hardware-related logs.                   |
| `esxcli system syslog reload`                              | Clear ESXi logs            | Reload the system logs after clearing.        |
| `esxtop -b`                                                | Check VM performance       | View performance metrics for VMs.             |
| `esxtop -m`                                                | Monitor memory usage       | Monitor memory usage for VMs.                 |


---

## 5. Networking and Security

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `esxcli network firewall ruleset list` | List firewall rules | Display all active firewall rules. |
| `esxcli network firewall ruleset set --ruleset-id=<ruleset_name> --enabled=true` | Enable a firewall rule | Enable a specific firewall rule on the host. |
| `vmkping <ip_address>` | Test network connectivity | Ping a network IP address to check connectivity. |
| `esxcli network ip dns search list` | Display DNS configuration | Show the DNS search configuration for the host. |
| `esxcli network vswitch standard portgroup list` | List VLANs | Display all VLANs on the host. |
| `esxcli network vswitch standard list` | View vSwitch statistics | Display traffic statistics for a virtual switch. |

