## 6. Storage Management

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `esxcli storage core device stats get --device=<device_name>` | Display storage statistics | Show performance stats for a storage device. |
| `esxcli storage vmfs extent list` | List VMFS datastores | Display all VMFS datastores. |
| `esxcli storage vmfs create --volume-label=<label> --device=<device_name>` | Create a VMFS datastore | Create a new VMFS datastore. |
| `esxcli storage vmfs unmount --volume-label=<label>` | Unmount a datastore | Unmount a VMFS datastore. |
| `esxcli storage core adapter rescan --adapter=<adapter_name>` | Rescan a storage adapter | Rescan a specific storage adapter for devices. |

---

## 7. Miscellaneous Commands

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `esxcli system settings advanced list` | Display ESXi configuration | Show advanced system settings. |
| `esxcli system service list` | List services | Show all running services on the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli software vib list` | Check installed VIBs | List all installed VMware Installation Bundles (VIBs). |
| `esxcli software vib update --depot=<depot_file>` | Update a VIB | Update a VIB using a depot file. |
| `esxcli system ntp start` | Start NTP service | Start the NTP service on the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli system ntp sync` | Sync time with NTP server | Sync the time on the ESXi host with an NTP server. |
| `vim-cmd vimsvc/license --show` | Display host license | Show the current ESXi host license information. |

---


